                    <abstract lang="eng">This paper deals with a well-known
problem in the discussion of argument linking, the flexibility that we find
with particular verbs, and the constraints governing the integration of verbs
with so-called argument structure constructions. We will show that traditional
approaches as well as construction grammar need additional machinery to deal
with variable argument linking. I will present an optimisation approach to
variable argument linking that uses construction grammar as format for
morphosyntax.</abstract>
